Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro said on Thursday that the government lacks the resources to fight wildfires in the Amazon rainforest after satellite images showed a record number of burning spots this year. In a speech broadcast live on Facebook, the president said the government is investigating the fires. He also said he never claimed non-governmental organisations were starting fires in the forest, saying he was only talking of his suspicions. Read: Raging fires and dark skies put Brazilâ€™s Bolsonaro in spotlight